Exhibit 99.1
FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE
CLEVELAND  Dec. 7, 2005  Agilysys, Inc. (NASDAQ: AGYS), a leading provider of enterprise computer technology solutions, announced today it has entered the China and Hong Kong markets through the purchase of the China and Hong Kong operations of Mainline Information Systems, Inc. The business specializes in IBM information technology enterprise solutions for large and medium-sized businesses and banking institutions in the China market, and has sales offices in Beijing, Guangzhou, Shanghai and Hong Kong.
"The business provides the opportunity for Agilysys to quickly begin operations in China with a nucleus of local talented people," said Arthur Rhein, chairman, president and chief executive officer of Agilysys.
