Wild Empire, LLC
As discussed under Note 1, Wild Empire became a wholly-owned subsidiary in 2005. Due to lack of revenue generated by Wild Empire, in late 2005 the Company discontinued its operations. Property and equipment, including production equipment, with a net carrying value of $0.1 million was written-off in connection with the discontinuance of Wild Empire's operations. Additionally, exit costs of $0.5 million relating to operating lease commitments were recognized with the discontinuance of Wild Empire's operations. Both costs have been classified as a component of discontinued operations in the accompanying consolidated income statement.
