Liability
 means, with respect to any Person, any Indebtedness, liability, claim or obligation of such Person of any kind, character or description, whether known or unknown, absolute or contingent, accrued or unaccrued, disputed or undisputed, liquidated or unliquidated, direct or indirect, secured or unsecured, joint or several, due or to become due, currently existing or arising in the future, vested or unvested, executory, determined, determinable or otherwise, and whenever or however arising (including whether arising by operation of law, or out of any Contract, tort, product liability, infringement, environmental claim or Taxes) and whether or not the same would be required by GAAP to be stated in financial statements or disclosed in the notes thereto, or otherwise.
