(c)
    
The Business Intellectual Property, together with (i) the Licensed Intellectual Property, (ii) any Intellectual Property which can be used by the Buyer to conduct the Business without infringing the Intellectual Property Rights of any third party without entering into any license agreement, (iii) the Retained Names, and (iv) the Excluded Intellectual Property, includes all of the Intellectual Property used by the Seller in connection with the Business or is necessary for the operation of the Business, and there are no other items of Intellectual Property that are material to the operation of the Business.
